# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# 1. In Roo Code chat, type slash commands:
#    /architect - For architecture and system design
#    /code      - For writing code
#    /research  - For deep analysis and research
#    /quick     - For quick questions
#    /debug     - For debugging issues
#    /reverse   - For reverse engineering
#    /optimize  - For performance optimization
#
# 2. Roo Code automatically switches to the right model!
#
# 3. The "Sticky Models" feature remembers which model you used
#    for each mode, so you don't have to configure it again.
#
# EXAMPLES:
#
# /architect Design a microservices architecture for e-commerce
# /code Implement JWT authentication in Python
# /research Compare Redis vs Memcached for session storage
# /quick What's the syntax for Python async/await?
# /debug Why is this function returning None?
# /reverse Analyze this network packet capture
# /optimize Make this database query faster
